      "name": "Construct stiffness validation — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against mean experimental stiffness from N=11 specimens (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). Predicted value 312.4 N/mm versus experimental mean 308.7 N/mm (1.2% difference). E/uval = 0.41, well within the acceptance threshold of 1.96. Aleatory uncertainty arising from specimen-to-specimen geometric variability and material lot differences was quantified via Monte Carlo propagation of measured dimensional tolerances (±0.05 mm) and reported titanium alloy elastic modulus distribution (CV=3.2%).",
