      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force compared against experimental yield force across N=11 constructs. Predicted 1842 N versus experimental mean 1879 N (2.0% difference). E/uval = 0.88, within the 1.96 acceptance bound. Aleatory uncertainty from material yield strength variability was quantified using a normal distribution fit to coupon tensile data (mean 930 MPa, SD 18 MPa) and propagated through the nonlinear FEA via Latin hypercube sampling (n=200 runs).",
