      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement validation — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw",
      "description": "FEA-predicted force at 40 mm crosshead displacement compared against experimental values (N=11 constructs). Predicted 2104 N versus experimental mean 2071 N (1.6% difference). E/uval = 0.73, within the 1.96 acceptance bound. Inherent variability in the experimental force-displacement response at large deformations — attributable to inter-specimen differences in screw seating depth, polyaxial head engagement angle, and UHMWPE block density — was assessed qualitatively by the test engineers based on visual inspection of the force-displacement curves and inter-laboratory scatter; no formal probabilistic UQ model was constructed for this quantity of interest.",
