    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-fda-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by the direct correspondence of the single ASTM F1717 test configuration to the COU and by the strong E/uval performance across all three QoIs. All three ValidationResults satisfy the pre-specified acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96; QoI difference < 10%). The credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion and the decision to accept the FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
